
  Debian users can install and upgrade Pure-FTPd with apt-get .
  
  Intel precompiled binaries are available, as well as source code.

  Just edit your /etc/apt/sources.conf file and add these lines :
  
deb     ftp://ftp.pureftpd.org/pub/pure-ftpd/debian/ ./
deb-src ftp://ftp.pureftpd.org/pub/pure-ftpd/debian/ ./

  Now, you can enjoy "apt-get install pure-ftpd", "apt-get upgrade pure-ftpd",
and "apt-get source pure-ftpd" . 